column10: Wang, Fei; Ma, Xuzhou; Wang, Wu; Liu, Jiyuan
column11: INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF FOOD SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY
column24: A) Four wild longsnout catfish were studied. All fish about 3 years old and similar body size were obtained from freshwater in May 2010. Wild fish (weight: 711 ± 81 g and length: 37.6 ± 2.0 cm, respectively) were captured from the Xiling Gorge of the Yangtze River (China). B) Each fish was separately filleted, skinned, homogenised and packed in the polyethylene bag and stored at -20C for further analyses.
column141: A) Analyses for proximate composition were performed on fresh fillets. Proximate composition (%, wet weight). Values are mean ± SE (n = 4). B) Fatty acid composition (% total fatty acids) in the fillets of wild longsnout catfish. Values are mean ± SE (n = 4).

column24: A) The fish samples were caught from River Galma, Zaria in the northern part of Nigeria between the months of January and May (dry season). The fishes were eviscerated with the heads, tails, fins and scales also removed before being minced along with the bones.
